<TITLE> 'Tahrir leader' arrested in Ctg </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 30 (bdnews24.com) -- The Detective Branch of police arrested a man in the early hours of Sunday claiming him to be a leader of banned militant group Hizb ut-Tahrir. Amiruzzaman Parvez, 31, from Tayabbagh residential area of Panchlaish union, however claimed to the police that he is only a follower of the organisation. Jahangir Alam, the assistant commissioner of Chittagong DB police, said Parvez was a Tahrir leader of Chittagong branch in a press briefing on Sunday. He told bdnews24.com they had arrested Parvez while he was in a secret meeting with some Tahrir members. The associates of Parvez managed to escape, he said, Police recovered a number of militant leaflets, a mobile phone and a laptop from the spot. Parvez was identified as the son of Mohammad Yeasin. Chittagong DB police told bdnews24.com that Parvez has been associated with the organisation since 2005. bdnews24
